The Gauteng Education Department says 99-percent of schools have opened without glitches. Next week, more pupils will return to school, after a four-week precautionary break. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department says 99-percent of schools have opened without glitches. Next week, more pupils will return to school, after a four-week precautionary break. READ: COVID-19 Education Crisis Committee calls for schools to shut down Gauteng Education head of department Edward Mosuwe says 78-percent of special education needs schools have also opened. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.